programmes.show_description: This Is CBeebies. Programmes start at 6.00am.
Shadow House. It's a hot day, so Tish imagines a 'shadow house' that her and Bobby can escape the heat in.
Kite. Children's animation. It's a windy day, and Bing wants to fly his Hoppity Voosh kite with Flop. And he wants to do it all by himself.
Tickly. Preschool series. The Teletubbies enjoy doing Round and Round the Garden, especially the end of the rhyme where they all tickle each other.
Piano. Preschool animation about a baby monkey and his mother. Mo loves playing the piano, and Tee wants to help Mo play the piano too. This could lead to some interesting music!
Banana's Star Appeal. Supertato and Carrot help a superstar banana get his peel back from Evil Pea.
Fossil. Sula finds a beautiful fossil in the Howly Woods, so Bing wants to find one too.
The Swoppiton Duck. A big duck statue needs pulling up treacherous Swoppiton Hill. Will Mojo and Bo make it?
Calm Down. Water, water, everywhere - there's a flood in our hospital soap opera! Grown-up Tag the firefighter splashes around. It's a good job grown-up Happy the lifeguard is on hand.
The Cheese Badge. Duggee and the Squirrels go on a mission to contain an outbreak.
Perfect. Bluey's Father's Day card has to be perfect, but she can't decide what to draw.
Helicopter. At school, Bluey and her friends turn a tree stump into a thrilling helicopter game. But as the pilot, Bluey has to learn to give up some control so they can all have fun. .
Go Jetter Heroes: Polar Explorers. Kyan and Glitch race to the South Pole in this chilly Antarctic adventure.
The Tale of the Puddleduck Disaster. Animated series. When Jemima is short on flapjack ingredients, she misunderstands Peter's advice and heads to Mr McGregor's garden.
Yellowstone Wolves. The Octonauts must chase away some hungry wolves while in the Yellowstone ecosystem.
All the Numbers I Can Be. One is in awe of how many numbers One Hundred has inside - but exactly how many are there? One Hundred takes her on a journey to find out.
Glow. The adventures of 26 lively letters who can make words come to life by holding hands. When O and F turn the lights off, how will they get them back on?   Followed by Tiny Wonders.
Time Warp. Travel through time with my Time Warp Challenge. Are you ready to time jump through arm circles, runners and toe tap, before heading back to the future for the Activate?
Pockets. Bella and Lift visit Patch in the Cloud Kitchen. He has found a tiny mouse in his pocket, which reminds him of a tasty treat recipe to make with the Playtimers - pocket mouse pitta!
Pak Choi. Live from the Roots and Fruits theatre, it's your favourite show host Pak Choi, who might be known by many names but sings about how she's Always Pak Choi to You!
Choosing. Children's animation. Bing has enough money to buy one thing in Padget's shop, but he finds it hard to choose between all the lovely things.
Gloves. Dee encourages a friend to say 'gloves', and we go on a whirlwind word adventure! We see gold gloves, spotty gloves, kitten mitten gloves and help Dee find her other glove.
The Big Laugh. Lu upsets Elodie when she laughs at an involuntary noise she makes.
Fine Forest Gift Tree. Wilf asks the Piggies to build a vehicle with a big basket - he wants to use it to steal all the gifts at the Fine Forest party! The Piggies must get them back.
More About Coming and Going. Stop-motion preschool programme. The Twirlywoos are watching a man flying his model aeroplane. They watch it coming and going as it flies overhead.
Autumn. Educational series using Makaton sign language. Justin has lots of autumn fun with his friends, but Mr Tumble can't play football because leaves are blocking the goal.
Number Four. Preschool series. The Teletubbies count to four - four flowers, four pieces of tubby toast. In Tummy Tales, two sisters help their dad put a number four on their door.
Shiny. Nigel and Baby Bear invite babies and their grown-ups to explore things that are shiny through discovery, play, song and story. Little ones and grown-ups at home can join in too!
Camping. Elsee plays I-spy whilst on a camping trip with her new friend Theodore.
Leaves. While playing in the garden, Maddie and Triggs make a new friend named Reginald. They soon discover that crunchy leaves mean much more to this tiny little caterpillar.
Sports Shop Owner. Dylan the sports shop owner wants to sell all the merchandise in his store. But when a five-armed customer comes in, he's going to have to pull out all the stops!
Mother Earth. Lou is saved by Kiri from a nightmare in which the Earth seems to have a mind of its own.
Coconut Roll. Ginger must navigate chaos amid rolling Coconutdons and tail-swatting Pineapplesauruses.
Backpackers. Mum and Dad are going on an adventure wearing the kids as their cheeky backpacks!
The Opposites Badge. The Squirrels learn what opposites are with the help of some topsy-turvy animal friends!
The Planet of the Floating Islands. Where are the children on a mysterious planet with colourful puffs of air?
Timmy's Pet Problem. Animated adventures of a lamb at nursery school. Timmy finds an old mop head and is convinced that it is a little animal, which he adopts as his pet.
George and Freddie's Snow Day. George and Freddie have an exciting day with Grandma when it starts to snow!
Iaia's Guinea-Bissau Kansiye. Iaia is cooking a delicious stew from Guinea-Bissau called kansiye. The tasty dish is made with lentils and served with rice and carrots.

programmes.show_name: Ferne and Rory's Teeny Tiny Creatures
programmes.show_description: Woodlice. Rory and Sandy hunt eco-friendly woodlice and build a bug hotel. Ferne meets crayfish.
Mission: Stormy Mountain. Dan and Jamie race to find some hikers to warn them about an approaching storm.
Vulture and Brittlestar. Aneeshwar and Lizzie meet two amazing animals and reveal a surprising connection between them in the wild. This time, it's vultures and brittlestars.
Waffle's Playdate. Evie, Waffle, Ruby and Jelly have a playdate. Mrs Hobbs has a delivery disaster.
To See the Moon. Oona really wants to stay up to see the moon tonight - it's a supermoon!
Small Potato Rock. Animated series about a group of singing potatoes. In this upbeat hip-hop song, the Small Potatoes introduce themselves and sing about their unique personalities.
Cleo Nibbles. A soul singer is coming to perform in the garden, but no one knows what they look like.
The Collecting Badge. Animated preschool series. When they see Duggee cleaning his biscuit tin collection, the Squirrels are inspired to start their own collections.
Dog. Preschool series about words. Dee encourages a friend to say 'dog', and we go on a whirlwind word adventure exploring how dogs look and what they do.
As Tall as the Sun. Six and her friends are growing sunflowers, but some are taller than others. Using a ladder, they measure whose sunflower is the tallest and learn about measuring length.
Champ. Educational fun. CH and SH go head to head in the Alphablocks Games and pit a ship and a shop against a chip and a chop.
Monkeying Around. Justin spends the day with a monkey-loving friend, while Mr Tumble has fun playing hide-and-seek with the toys.
Rolling. Preschool series. Laa-Laa and Po have fun, first rolling a ball down a hill and then rolling each other!
Patchwork Clam. Patchwork Clam has a problem - she can't play because she is way too shy! Will the Patchwork Pals find a way to make her come out of her shell?
Raa Raa and Crocky's Lost Toy. Animation set in the Jingly Jangly Jungle. When Raa Raa loses Crocky's favourite toy, he's determined to find it again.
Glow Koko. When Mtambo takes Koko, Piper and Hodge on a night tour through Safari Park, Koko discovers a new world of Chuggington that glows in the dark.
Episode 1. Comedy sketch show for younger viewers. Ants are on the loose in the newsroom, making it tricky for Arthur Sleep to read news.
Beach Machines. In this episode, Grace shows off three incredible machines that all belong on the beach.
The Magnetic Planet. The Game Catchers arrive on the Magnetic Planet to play submarines.
Manatees. Animated deep sea adventures with Captain Barnacles and his explorers. Running out of air, Barnacles struggles to free his paw from the mouth of a giant clam.
The Tale of Jemima's Egg. Animated series. When Peter is asked to watch Jemima's egg, he discovers that babysitting is far more dangerous than he could ever have imagined.
The Shadow Badge. Animated preschool series. There's been a power cut and the Squirrels can't see anything. Thank goodness Duggee has got his torch.
Sunny's Big Feelings. Sunny wants to win a box car race but doesn't feel like his team is taking it seriously.
Supertato's Holiday. Supertato goes on holiday but can't relax because Evil Pea is sure to do something evil.
Mission Camping. Weasy promises to go camping with the Ducklings, but he wants to watch football instead. During half-time, Weasy attempts to finish camping as quickly as possible.
Big Top Bo. Tao can't go on with his circus performance, so there are going to be some disappointed fans, unless Bo agrees to do all the acts for him - with some help from Mojo's tops!
Perfect. Bluey's Father's Day card has to be perfect, but she can't decide what to draw.
Movies. It is Bluey's first trip to the cinema, but Bingo starts running amok in the theatre.
The Millie Mix-Up. The Piris find their holiday home double-booked by penguin nemesis Millie the Squid.
Andy and the Hermit Crab. Preschool wildlife series. When a shell for an orphaned hermit crab accidentally gets broken, it's up to Andy to find a suitable replacement.
Moving Waffle. Preschool comedy drama series. Waffle is not allowed to go on a family camping trip but accidentally goes on a different adventure.
The Stuck Together Wish. Rafi wishes her play date with Ruby could last forever. Stuck together, they realise that even best friends have differences - and that's what makes them special.
It's Time to Help at the Farm. JoJo and Lexi visit the farm with Gran Gran, who helps Lucy the llama keep cosy!
Bug Bop. Animation. Bug and his friends lead Sarah and Duck to their outdoor music concert.
The Ball. Stop-motion animation. Tiny and Small find a strange silver ball. When it bounces it glows and rings. It bounces into Mother's garden.
Stars. BaBa has never seen a shooting star, so MeMo and BaBa go on a hunt to find one. BaBa's patience pays off just before BeddyByes time.
Oh Look! It's the Wottingers! In a magical forest, colourful characters have adventures. The Wottingers call on the Pontipines but there is no reply, so they go looking for them.
Scott Mills - What Makes a Lemur Listen. Join BBC Radio 2 DJ Scott Mills for a story about a lovable lemur who learns to listen.
This Is CBeebies. Programmes start at 6.00am.
All at Sea. Tish offers to help her mum with a painting she is finding difficult to finish.
More. Children's animation. At bath time, Bing just cannot help adding a few more squirts of bubble goo, and a few more, until he gets more bubbles than he can handle.
Spinning. Preschool series. The Teletubbies travel by Tubby Car to the Hidey Hup, where they all spin around on the Tubby Spinny.
Big Boy Tee. Preschool animation about a baby monkey and his mother. Tee and Mo are having a picnic, but Tee spots his friends and wants to journey across the park... on his own!
Spooky Day. Supertato is scared when Pumpkin tries to make friends with him.
Nicky. Bing shows Sula's cousin how to voosh a toy car down a slide - but then things go wrong.
Happy Happy Valentine's. Mojo and Bo have to deliver a superfun singing valentine. But the problem is, they don't know who it's for, or who it's from. Preston is racing to beat them to it!
Master of Puppets. At Squirrel Club, there's a story told in blocks, the tale of a first tooth, a fable about changing emotions, and a yarn involving the Squirrels as puppets.
The Radio Badge. The Squirrels find some of Duggee's radio equipment and decide to start their own show.
Explorers. While waiting to be picked up from school, Jack plays at being a sailor lost at sea.
Sleepytime. Bingo and Floppy have an intergalactic adventure in Bingo's dream, while the rest of her sleep-deprived family try to navigate Bingo's nonstop night-time bed-hopping.
Middle of the World City, Ecuador. Glitch is out to prove he's just as good as the Go Jetters when he heads to Ecuador and moves the Monument to the Equator.
The Tale of the Squirrel Hotpot. Animated series. Mr Tod catches Squirrel Nutkin and takes him to Owl Island to get a squirrel recipe from Old Brown.
Bald Ibises. Tracker spots some northern bald ibises migrating in the wrong direction.
The Rings of Unity. The Numberblocks Space Division are investigating a signal - until a strange planet splits them into hundreds, tens and ones. How can they escape?
Sing. The adventures of 26 lively letters who can make words come to life by holding hands. B, D and N form a band, but they still need a singer.   Followed by Tiny Wonders.
ExtraStretchy. Flex and bend into my ExtraStretchy Challenge. Stretch your skills with arm circles, lunges and toe taps, then get flexible in the Activate!
Ball. Bella and Lift have fun playing with their favourite red bouncy ball. It drops into the Ice Disco, giving Hettie the Yeti an idea for a bouncy dance!
Parsley. Live from the Roots and Fruits theatre, it's Parsley performing Rise Up with Me.
Dark. Children's animation. It is bedtime, but where is Hoppity? Bing remembers playing with him in the garden, but now it is dark out there and he doesn't really like the dark.
Scooter. Dee encourages a friend to say 'scooter', and we go on a whirlwind word adventure. There's a purple scooter, a fast scooter and even a hopping scooter!
Power Flower. Declan gets carried away when he's put in charge of an all-powerful flower.
Cherry's Show. The Piggies build Cherry a stage but forget to plan her show!
More About Underneath. Stop-motion preschool programme. The Twirlywoos are in a warehouse, underneath a cardboard box, when a man tries to load them into a lorry.
Music Stars. Educational series using Makaton sign language. Justin and some musical friends put on a concert. Meanwhile, Mr Tumble is the judge of Tumbleton's Got Talent!
Flying. Preschool series. The Teletubbies pretend to fly. Po goes so fast on the scooter that it starts to fly over Teletubbyland! The children in Tummy Tales watch swans flying.
Day Out. Babies and their grown-ups play with things themed around a day out.
Dairy Farm. Elsee visits a farm with her friend Hugo and plays a game of I-spy.
Waves. While playing at the beach, Maddie and Triggs try to save their sandcastle from the incoming tide, so it can be a fancy home for their magical new friend, Sailor Nancy.
Construction Worker. Dylan the construction worker wants to build the tallest building ever.
The Indescribable. Pania's Uncle Tama is very old and seems ready for a sleep.
Top of the Pops. Ginger and the baby Pea-Rexes help a young Cornasaurolophus reach the top of a volcano.
The Adventure. Princesses, horses and magic wands. Bluey and Chloe can play any role they want, when they embark on an adventure to save their playground kingdom from the Greedy Queen.
The Breakfast Badge. Tag is feeling grumpy because he didn't eat his breakfast. Luckily, Duggee has his Breakfast Badge, and soon the Squirrels will too.
Don't Dance There! The Game Catchers jump right into playing land and sea with their turnip alien friends.
Count on Timmy. Animated adventures of a lamb at nursery school. Timmy and Finlay both have their hearts set on a toy plane, so they try to raise enough buttons to buy it.
George and Freddie Play Dino-Tennis. Mum and Dad challenge George and Freddie to an unusual game of dino-tennis.
Elsa's Guyanese Fishcakes. Elsa is making a traditional Guyanese recipe using salt fish, potatoes and chives.

programmes.show_name: Ferne and Rory's Teeny Tiny Creatures
programmes.show_description: Ladybirds. Rory and Sandy look for top pest controllers: ladybirds. Ferne meets some beetles.
Mission: Football Match. It's the Woofton Wolves's last football match of the season, and Rayane is in danger of missing the second half. Can hearing dog Diesel help him save the game?
Owl Butterfly and Sunbittern. Aneeshwar and Lizzie meet two amazing animals and reveal a surprising connection between them. This time, it's the giant owl butterfly and the sunbittern.
PE Waffle. Evie forgets her reading book, so Waffle takes it to her at school. As Waffle reaches the playground, he sees Evie's PE class and is desperate to join in.
The Shiny Shell. Baba finds a beautiful, shiny shell that causes some seagull trouble for Oona.
Seasons. Animated series about a group of singing potatoes. The Potatoes celebrate the four seasons and sing a folksy song about the exciting things that come with each one!
March of the Ants. Twinkle and Yukee try to stop marching ants from taking seeds from the vegetable garden.
The Theatre Badge. Animated preschool series. Tino and Eugene are having a disagreement about an amateur dramatic show they want to put on. Can Duggee and the Squirrels help them?
Book. Preschool series about words. Dee encourages a friend to say 'book', and we go on a whirlwind word adventure, encountering lots of books and exploring how they look.
Feeding Time. The Numberblocks transport block fruit to Blockzilla and learn about weight using a pair of balancing scales.
Song. Educational fun. The Alphablocks join in with a singalong song, in which birds sing and bells ring.
Dinosaurs. Justin and his friends go to a dinosaur park, while Mr Tumble visits Shopkeeper Tumble.
Conga. Preschool series. The Teletubbies do conga dances over the hills, then they conga into Home Dome to answer the Tubby Phone and do a special conga Tubby Phone Dance.
Patchwork Spider. Patchwork Spider has a problem: he wants to play music on his net, but the music sounds bad! Will the Patchwork Pals find a way to help him?
Raa Raa and Hooting Huffty. Animation set in the Jingly Jangly Jungle. Huffty's not feeling well and can't stop sneezing. Raa Raa finds a way to make his sneezes part of the fun!
Not from Around Here. When a new chugger Rosa comes to Chuggington, the trainees try to help her find a job that she will love in her new city.
Episode 2. Comedy sketch show for younger viewers. Accident-prone DIY Dan attempts to build a kennel for his little dog.
Transport Machines. Grace goes underground to drive a tube train, shows off a hanging railway and then drives a hydrogen boat.
The Book Planet. The Game Catchers land on Book Planet and learn to play tower of cups, but the game is interrupted after a lost Sparkstar needs help finding the book it came from!
Saltwater Crocodile. Animated deep sea adventures with Captain Barnacles and his explorers. The Octonauts must figure out how to get a gigantic saltwater crocodile back home.
The Tale of the Lucky Four-Leaf Clover. Animated series. When Benjamin finds a four-leaf clover, Peter tricks him into thinking it brings good luck.
The Memory Badge. Animated preschool series. Happy's wobbly tooth has come out, but he's lost it! Time to think carefully and remember where he was when it fell out.
Pippen's Stuffed Up. Pippen is ready to sing at her concert - until her cold threatens to ruin the performance.
Disco Fog. Evil Pea fogs up the supermarket by using a fog machine so that Supertato and the Tato Team get lost forever - but she ends up getting lost herself.
Mission Magic. Weasy refuses to share his magic kit, so Spicy decides to put on her own magic show.
Panic at the Pumpkin Patch. Is there really a ghost at Jackson's pumpkin patch? Mojo and Bo need to find out!
Explorers. While waiting to be picked up from school, Jack plays at being a sailor lost at sea.
Library. When Muffin is told that she is special by her Dad, she uses it as an excuse to do anything she wants, which means playing Bluey and Bingo's library game her way.
One Flutter Too Many. When Flutter accidentally clones himself, the berg is flooded with misbehaving penguins.
Andy and the Catfish. Preschool wildlife series. When Mr Hammond's photo of a catfish is destroyed, Andy heads to a cave in Africa to track down a catfish and take a new picture.
Waffle and the Fleas. Preschool comedy drama series. The Brooklyn-Bells call on Mrs Hobbs to persuade her not to move house, only to find that her cat, George, has fleas.
The Do It All Wish. Rafi's wish to be in two places at once leads to mix-ups. She realises it's better to focus on one thing at a time.
It's Time to Remember Grandad. JoJo wants to know more about Grandad, so Gran Gran takes her on an adventure to remember him by doing all his favourite winter activities.
Duck Flies. Animation. Duck sees some migrating ducks flying in the sky. He decides he would like to try it too.
Planty. Stop-motion animation. The Clangers help Granny make her knitting space more special. Major makes her a fan and Mother gives her a purple plant from her garden.
Where's Yummy? MeMo and BaBa have fun spotting the Yummies, who are popping up everywhere today. The friends learn that their fun game is actually a hunt for Yummy Dog, who is missing.
Upsy Daisy Dances with the Haahoos. In a magical forest, colourful characters have adventures. Upsy Daisy is having a dancy day in the garden.
Joanne Froggatt - The World Needs Who You Were Made to Be. Joanne shares a beautiful story which celebrates our differences.
